# Scripts

All scripts live in `scripts/` at the repo root. Run them from anywhere; each resolves paths relative to the repo root.

## `scripts/build-firmware.sh`

Builds the ESP32 firmware with PlatformIO in `Firmware-PIO/`.

- Finds `pio` on PATH or at `~/.platformio/penv/bin/pio`
- Equivalent to `cd Firmware-PIO && pio run`
- Extra PlatformIO args are forwarded (e.g. `./scripts/build-firmware.sh -t upload`)

Use this instead of calling `pio` directly when you want a consistent entry point from the repo root.

## `scripts/update-web-installer.sh`

Refreshes the browser installer binaries in `docs/` after a successful build.

- Copies from `Firmware-PIO/.pio/build/esp32dev/`:
  - `bootloader.bin`
  - `partitions.bin`
  - `firmware.bin`
- Requires a prior build; exits with an error if any file is missing

Typical release workflow:

```bash
./scripts/build-firmware.sh
./scripts/update-web-installer.sh
# Bump "version" in docs/manifest.json, then commit docs/
```

The [browser installer](https://justinmahar.github.io/YouTube-Subscriber-Counter/) (esp-web-tools) serves these files from GitHub Pages. OTA updates on a flashed device use `firmware.bin` only; the browser installer flashes the full image.

## `scripts/preview-installer.sh`

Serves `docs/` locally to preview the browser installer before publishing.

- Default URL: `http://localhost:8765/`
- Optional port: `./scripts/preview-installer.sh 9000`
- Uses `python3 -m http.server`

Use this to verify `docs/index.html`, `docs/manifest.json`, and the `.bin` files without pushing to GitHub Pages.

## Deploy / Dev

If users says to prepare to deploy, do the following:
- Set DISABLE_INTRO_AND_WIFI_INFO to false
- Set ENABLE_WOKWI_SETUP to false

If users says to go back to development mode, do the following:
- Set DISABLE_INTRO_AND_WIFI_INFO to true
- Set ENABLE_WOKWI_SETUP to true

Then run the build the firmware.